       gradients are used to display smooth transition between two colors

       they are two types of gradients
       1 linear gradient
       2. radial gradient


       .test{
    height: 250px;
    background-color: red;
    background-image: linear-gradient(to bottom right,red,yellow);
}

</style>
<body>
  <div class="test">

  </div>

       radial gradient is defined by its center



       multiple backgrounds

       .test{
    height: 250px;

    background-image: url(dog.jpg),url(dog1.jpg),url(dog3.jpg);
    background-position: right bottom,left bottom,left top;
    background-size: 200px,200px,200px;
    background-repeat: no-repeat,no-repeat,no-repeat;
}

</style>
<body>
  <div class="test">

  </div>

2d trasformations

css allows us to move the html elements

translate()
rotate()
scale()
skew()
matrix(scex(),skewy(),skewx,scaley,translex,translaatey)

3d transformation has z-axis..


CSS allows animation without JS  and Flash

it changes the styles according to the timeframe from one to another style

@keyframes


example

    div{
        width:200px;
        height: 200px;
        background-color: rebeccapurple;
        animation-name: test;
        animation-duration: 4s;
        position: relative;
        animation-delay: 3s;
        animation-iteration-count: infinite;
        animation-direction: alternate;
    }
    @keyframes test{
        0%{background-color: rebeccapurple; left:0px;top: 0px;}
        25%{background-color: red;left: 300px; top: 0px;}
        50%{background-color: yellow;left: 300px;top: 300px;}
        75%{background-color: tomato;left: 0px; top: 300px;}
        100%{background-color: rebeccapurple; left:0px;top: 0px;}


    }

