@rules

the rule is a statement that provieds css with instructions to porform or to h=behave

@import url("hello.css")

@media
@charset "utf-8"

@font-face {
    font-family:'myownfont';
    src:url('myownfont.woff2')format(woff2)
}

pseudo class is  used to define a special state of the element

With the help pseudo class we can style an element when mouse over it

sytanx  :

selector:pseudoclass{


}

example  :

a:link{
    color:tomato;

}
a:visited{
    color: red;
}
a:active{
    color:blueviolet;
}
a:hover{
    color: chartreuse;
}

</style>
<body>

<div>
    <a href="https://www.google.com">Go to google</a>
</div>

sytax of psuedo element

p::psuedo-element{

}

media queries are extendetend version of media type

media type it onky helps to find the width of the device

media queries even look for the capability of the device.

1 width and height of the viewport
2. width and height of the device
orientation and resolution

 body{
        background-color: blueviolet;
    }
    @media screen and (min-width:780px){
        body{
        background-color: brown;
        }
    }

there two of user interface properties
1 resize
2.outline-offset

    p{
        border:1px solid black;
        outline: 2px solid red;
        padding:10px;
        margin-left:10px;
        outline-offset: 15px;
    }

without border sizing
   width+padding+border=actual width
   height+padding+border=actual height

    p{
        border:15px dashed black;
        padding:15px;
        border-image: url("frame2.png") 30 round;

    }

    1.image to use for the border
    2.slicing of image3. defining the middile section to repeat or not

    multi column property is used to create multiple column for text

    p{
        column-count: 3;
        column-gap: 30px;
        column-rule-style: solid;
        column-rule-width: 1px;
        column-rule-color: chartreuse;

    }




